1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,289
and the third was a brother-in-law.

2
00:00:02,880 --> 00:00:06,450
Next, again, I don't know what made me do this.

3
00:00:06,560 --> 00:00:12,769
I asked myself, what do my five friends have that I don't have, besides better jobs?

4
00:00:13,040 --> 00:00:19,970
I compared myself with them on intelligence, but I honestly couldn't see that they excelled in the brains department,

5
00:00:20,160 --> 00:00:26,529
nor could I truthfully say they had me beat on education, integrity, or personal habits.

6
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:32,529
Finally, I got down to another success quality one hears a lot about, initiative.

7
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:35,890
Here I hated to admit it, but I had to.

8
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:42,049
On this point, my record showed I was far below that of my successful friends.

9
00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:47,730
It was now about three a.m., but my mind was astonishingly clear.

10
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:51,010
I was seeing my weak point for the first time.

11
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:53,730
I discovered that I had held back.

12
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:56,370
I had always carried a little stick.

13
00:00:56,720 --> 00:01:06,370
I dug into myself deeper and deeper, and found the reason I lacked initiative was because I didn't believe inside that I was worth very much.

14
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:14,929
I sat there the rest of the night, just reviewing how lack of faith in myself had dominated me ever since I could remember.

15
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:18,690
How I had used my mind to work against myself.

16
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:24,610
I found I had been preaching to myself why I couldn't get ahead instead of why I could.

17
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:27,090
I had been selling myself short.

18
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:32,610
I found this streak of self-depreciation showed through in everything I did.

19
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:39,010
Then it dawned on me that no one else was going to believe in me until I believed in myself.

20
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:43,890
Right then I decided, I'm through feeling second class.

21
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,570
From here on in, I'm not going to sell myself short.

22
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:51,169
Next morning, I still had that confidence.

23
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:56,370
During the job interview, I gave my newfound confidence its first test.

24
00:01:56,640 --> 00:02:07,169
Before coming for the interview, I'd hoped I would have the courage to ask for $750 or maybe even $1,000 more than my present job was paying.

25
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:14,370
But now, after realizing I was a valuable man, I upped it to $3,500.

26
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:15,649
And I got it.

27
00:02:15,919 --> 00:02:24,689
I sold myself because, after that one long night of self-analysis, I found things in myself that made me a lot more saleable.

28
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:32,290
Within two years after I took that job, I had established a reputation as the fellow who can get business.

29
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,850
Then we went into a recession.

30
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:40,610
This made me still more valuable because I was one of the best business getters in the industry.

31
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:47,489
The company was reorganized and I was given a substantial amount of stock plus a lot more pay.

32
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:52,770
Believe in yourself and good things do start happening.

